		<div class="comment-body"><p>Chris, I don&#8217;t know anything about this subject but I can tell you that my family has a well in Kansas that belonged to my Grandfather that was capped because the production fell off back in the 70&#8242;s. Fast forward to 2010 &#8211; it was re-opened and pumping again. Your comment peaked my curiosity so I googled &#8220;oil wells refilling&#8221; and it does appear there are extensive articles on the subject. This is just one of thousands of articles&#8230;</p>
<p><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/1995/09/26/science/geochemist-says-oil-fieldsmay-be-refilled-naturally.html?pagewanted=all&#038;src=pm" rel="nofollow">http://www.nytimes.com/1995/09/26/science/geochemist-says-oil-fieldsmay-be-refilled-naturally.html?pagewanted=all&#038;src=pm</a></p>
<p>It might be insightful for you to read the above article. What I have found in 50 some odd years of life, is that those who use derogatory language to defend their position tend to be less informed. I don&#8217;t pretend know why oil wells refill but I know first hand that they in-fact do.</p>
