		<div class="comment-body"><p>I&#8217;m surprised that some listeners would question Jack&#8217;s decision to interview JHK, and question whether JHK shares the values of the TSP community.  Speaking personally, the tandem of JHK&#8217;s &#8220;Long Emergency&#8221; and Bill McKibben&#8217;s &#8220;Deep Economy&#8221; switched me onto the idea of prepping and connecting to a community a couple years before Jack started his podcast.  In &#8220;Too Much Magic&#8221; Kunstler admits to being a life-long democrate; as such he is insterested in the role government should have in transitioning our nation from an economy built on cheap energy to whatever the heck&#8217;s going to come next.  Rugged individuals who are hyper-sensitive to government interference probably won&#8217;t care to hear that.  But everyone here should take heart that in Kunstler we have a best-selling author who reaches a liberal audience who is sympathetic to our cause&#8211;a very good thing, indeed.</p>
